about.description:
Small and dependency free Python package to infer file type
and MIME type checking the magic numbers signature of a file or buffer.
This is a Python port from filetype Go package.
about.summary: Infer file type and MIME type of any file/buffer. No external dependencies.

name: filetype
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "filetype" %}
{% set version = "1.0.5" %}
{% set sha256 = "17a3b885f19034da29640b083d767e0f13c2dcb5dcc267945c8b6e5a5a9013c7" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: '{{ sha256 }}'

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - examples
    - filetype
    - filetype.types

about:
  home: https://github.com/h2non/filetype.py
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: '{{ environ["RECIPE_DIR"] }}/LICENSE'
  summary: Infer file type and MIME type of any file/buffer. No external dependencies.
  description:  |
    Small and dependency free Python package to infer file type 
    and MIME type checking the magic numbers signature of a file or buffer.
    This is a Python port from filetype Go package.
  doc_url: 'https://h2non.github.io/filetype.py/'
  dev_url: 'https://github.com/h2non/filetype.py'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers: 
    - druvus
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.15
